---
// WhyDemandGenix.astro - Differentiation section with method and efficiency messaging
---

<section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Main Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        Senior Attention. No Middlemen.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        You work directly with Lee - 20 years of B2B demand gen experience, treating your budget as carefully as his own.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Three Column Benefits -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-16">
      <!-- No Fluff -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-2 border-primary-100 hover:border-primary-600 transition-colors">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary-600 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">No Fluff</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          I focus on leading indicators that matter: qualified traffic, conversion rates, funnel velocity. The metrics that predict pipeline health.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- No Bloat -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-2 border-primary-100 hover:border-primary-600 transition-colors">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary-600 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">No Bloat</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          You pay for senior expertise and hands-on execution - not layers of account management or agency infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- No Wait -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-2 border-primary-100 hover:border-primary-600 transition-colors">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary-600 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">No Wait</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          I start diagnosing in days, executing in weeks. Fixed-scope sprints mean predictable timelines and clear deliverables.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The DemandGenix Method -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 shadow-sm mb-16 section-divider">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">My 3-Step Framework to Fix Your Pipeline</h3>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Step 1: Diagnose -->
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3">
              1
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Diagnose</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-medium">Days 1-10</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            I tear down your ad accounts, analytics, and funnel to find the leaks and quick wins.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2: Build -->
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3">
              2
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Build</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-medium">Days 11-30</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Kill the wasted spend, fix tracking, and launch high-intent campaigns.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3: Scale -->
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3">
              3
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Scale</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-medium">Ongoing</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            I layer on new channels and optimise for revenue, not just clicks and vanity metrics.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Built for Efficiency Section -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        The Era of "Growth at All Costs" is Over
      </h3>
    </div>

    <!-- Three Efficiency Boxes -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-8">
      <!-- Lower CAC -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-secondary-600">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary-600 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"/>
          </svg>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Investors Want Lower CAC</h4>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Customer Acquisition Cost must decrease to prove your business model scales sustainably.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Clear Metrics -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-secondary-600">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary-600 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-6 9l2 2 4-4"/>
          </svg>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Founders Need Clear Metrics</h4>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          "What's actually working?" shouldn't be guesswork. Visibility into leading indicators and funnel health is essential.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Demonstrate Progress -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-secondary-600">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary-600 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
          </svg>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Marketing Must Demonstrate Progress</h4>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Boardrooms demand evidence of momentum - improving conversion rates, qualified pipeline building, efficient spend.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Closer Paragraph -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
        DemandGenix was built specifically to solve the "Efficiency Gap." We help you build demand generation foundations and identify what's working without burning cash on long experiments or vanity metrics.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>